name: Twice-a-week Method
description: Capping calories at 500 two days a week

name: Alternate day fasting
description: Modified fasting every other day.  Limit your calories on fasting days to 500 or 25% of your normal intake

name: Time-restricted eating: 16/8 or 14/10
description: Setting fasting windows.  For example, the 16/8 method means only eat between 11 a.m. and 7 p.m. or noon and 8p.m.  The 14/10 method means only eat between 10 a.m. and 8 p.m.

name: The 24-hour fast (or eat: stop: eat method)
description: This method involves fasting completely for a full 24 hours once or twice a week.
